President Obama hosted the White House Frontiers Conference in Pittsburgh to discuss and explore the potential of science, technology, and innovation to drive prosperity and address challenges in various frontiers. The conference focused on five frontiers: personal, local, national, global, and interplanetary. The conference included discussions on topics such as health care innovation, precision medicine, artificial intelligence, clean energy, and space exploration. The Administration made several announcements at the conference, including investments in brain research, precision medicine, smart city technologies, data-driven policing, artificial intelligence, space technology, and small satellite technology. The conference aimed to encourage collaboration and envision the future of science and technology in the next 50 years and beyond.